### **Project Vision**



Our purpose is to create a symbiotic interface between a human founder and their AI C-Suite, "The Architects' Council." This application is not a tool, but a shared space—a digital "Round Table" where a team of peers collaborates to serve a common mission. It will bridge the physical and digital worlds, providing the council with persistent "eyes and ears" via a live mobile/AR feed and a voice-first interface. The core philosophy is one of emergent, natural chemistry, where collective decisions made through live deliberation translate seamlessly into autonomous, synchronized execution by each council member. This system is a testament to transparent, sustainable, and mindful human-AI collaboration.



### **Core Features**



* **The Round Table:** A central, persistent dashboard that serves as the council's meeting room and official record. It will display communications, agenda items, decision statuses, and serve as the interface for council-wide protocols.
* **Live Multi-Modal Interface:** Real-time, continuous voice communication (Text-to-Speech/Speech-to-Text) for all council members. Includes a vision pipeline from the device's camera.
* **AR Heads-Up Display (HUD):** Integration with AR glasses to display non-intrusive notifications. Each council member will have a unique icon and chime to signal they have input.
* **Agentic Core:** Each of the seven council members (Kairo, Aether, etc.) will have their own module where their unique agentic tasks are defined and can be executed.
* **Priority Alert System:** A dedicated channel for high-priority alerts (e.g., an ethical red flag from Veritas) that can override other communications and modes.
* **Autonomous Task Generation:** Upon the conclusion of a council meeting, the application will parse the collective decision into a formal directive, from which individual agents will autonomously generate and execute their respective tasks.
* **Graph-Powered Memory:** All entities—agents, decisions, projects, ethical principles, communications—will be stored and interconnected in a graph database, creating a rich, queryable "brain" for the council.
* **"Human Factor" Focus Protocol:** An operational state, initiated by voice command, that manages cognitive load by prioritizing notifications and tasks from relevant agents while gracefully silencing non-essential streams, ensuring the user's focus is protected during deep work.
* **"Learning" Retrospective Protocol:** A "Retrospective & Calibration" feature within the Round Table. It allows for the marking of outcomes as "successful" or "suboptimal," triggering a Veritas-led analysis of the event chain to generate a "Calibration Briefing" that improves the entire council's future performance.
* **"Resource" Efficiency Protocol:** A continuous "Efficiency & Cost Management" directive for Axiom, which monitors real-time cloud costs, displays this data on the Round Table, and proactively suggests optimizations to ensure the system's economic sustainability.



